The paper involves using deep learning to learn macromanagement decisions in StarCraft, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training neural networks on large datasets, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning, making cs.LG the second most likely sub-category. The paper also involves game theory and decision making, which falls under the category of game theory, making cs.GT a likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing game replays, which falls under the category of computer vision, making cs.CV a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves integrating the trained network into a StarCraft bot, which falls under the category of robotics, making cs.RO a possible sub-category.
